This rifle is in almost new condition.  It has been fired sparingly, has been well cared for, and it functions perfectly.  There are a few very minor usage and handling marks here and there.  The bluing is near perfect.  The stock is a very nice piece of walnut.  This rifle has been a "safe queen" for the past three decades.   
Unlike earlier Model 94's, the 94AE ejects cartridges from the side rather than from the top, so it can easily accommodate a scope if desired.  The top of this receiver was drilled and tapped at the factory for scope mounts.  
This rifle does not have the dreaded cross-bolt safety that Winchester introduced in 1992.  Nor does it have the tang safety that was introduced in later models.
I don't expect to be shooting this rifle in the future, so it needs to find a good home.  I am asking $450.  Buyer must be an Arizona resident, non-felon,  21 years old.  CASH only.  Not interested in trades.
